Undiscovered is the debut album by English singer-songwriter James 
Morrison, released in the United Kingdom on 10 July 2006. In its first week he 
sold 84,611 albums in the UK. It's been certificated Gold in Australia and New 
Zealand and platinum in the United Kingdom and Ireland. The first single of 
this album was "You Give Me Something" and the second single is "Wonderful 
World". The third single released was "The Pieces Don't Fit Anymore" on 13 
December 2006. It sold 847,135 copies in the United Kingdom in 2006, 
bringing its total sales count to over 1,000,000 as of 12 March 2007.
